# Lab / compose: Kitchen API → Jupiter operator control plane (DV-077 / DV-072)
# Copy into your .env next to docker-compose and set values for your Jupiter host.
#
# KITCHEN_JUPITER_CONTROL_BASE must match the exact base URL of the Sean jupiter-web
# process whose SQLite DB backs the Jupiter trade UI — scheme + host + port, e.g.
# http://127.0.0.1:8788
#
# If Kitchen shows one active policy and the Jupiter trade surface shows another
# (e.g. jup_mc_test) after refresh, this base almost always points at the wrong host
# (common mistake: http://127.0.0.1:8080 = BlackBox api, which is NOT Sean Jupiter).
# Kitchen GET/POST must hit the same origin you open in the browser for Jupiter.
KITCHEN_JUPITER_CONTROL_BASE=
# Token must match Sean's JUPITER_OPERATOR_TOKEN (same as Kitchen → Jupiter POST Bearer).
KITCHEN_JUPITER_OPERATOR_TOKEN=
